President Donald J. Trump has announced his intent to nominate William Perry Pendley as the Director of the Bureau of Land Management. Pendley currently serves as the Deputy Director for Policy and Programs at the Bureau of Land Management, where he has focused on increasing recreational opportunities on public lands and addressing the impact of wild horses and burros. Pendley has previously served as the President of the Mountain States Legal Foundation and as Deputy Assistant Secretary of the Interior for Energy and Minerals in the Reagan administration.

President Trump also intends to nominate Allen Dickerson as a Member of the Federal Election Commission. Dickerson is currently the Legal Director at the Institute for Free Speech and has experience in First Amendment litigation. He also serves as a Captain in the Judge Advocate General's Corps of the United States Army Reserve.

In addition to nominations, President Trump plans to appoint Bill Haslam as a Member and Chairman of the Woodrow Wilson International Center for Scholars in the Smithsonian Institution. Haslam is from Tennessee.

Lastly, President Trump intends to appoint John H. Frey as a Member of the Advisory Council on Historic Preservation. Frey is from Connecticut.